344
00:37:39,510 --> 00:37:40,886
No.

345
00:37:40,969 --> 00:37:42,554
You told them nothing, right?

346
00:37:42,638 --> 00:37:44,556
Right.

347
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:47,184
Of course...

348
00:37:47,267 --> 00:37:50,896
you couldn't talk.

349
00:37:50,979 --> 00:37:52,773
Yeah.

350
00:37:57,361 --> 00:37:59,071
Let's keep it that way.

351
00:38:58,380 --> 00:39:00,841
I picked them
from the garden outside.

352
00:39:00,924 --> 00:39:03,844
I hope you don't mind.

353
00:39:03,927 --> 00:39:06,847
I didn't know
if you like coffee...

354
00:39:06,930 --> 00:39:08,473
or tea,
so I made both.

355
00:39:21,528 --> 00:39:24,198
I hope you like, uh...

356
00:39:24,281 --> 00:39:26,783
"Ma-de-leine."

357
00:39:26,909 --> 00:39:28,869
Try one.

358
00:39:31,914 --> 00:39:33,373
Careful.

359
00:39:33,457 --> 00:39:34,666
It's hot.

360
00:39:37,628 --> 00:39:39,046
Good?

361
00:39:45,135 --> 00:39:46,553
Let me.

362
00:39:48,430 --> 00:39:50,182
I like it quiet in the morning.

363
00:39:50,265 --> 00:39:52,309
Yes.
Quiet in the morning.

364
00:39:52,392 --> 00:39:53,727
Me, too.
Me, too.

365
00:39:53,810 --> 00:39:57,439
I'm the same way.
I like very quiet.

366
00:39:59,608 --> 00:40:01,443
Sorry.

367
00:40:07,407 --> 00:40:08,951
Are you looking for milk?

368
00:40:10,244 --> 00:40:12,496
There's milk at the door.

369
00:40:12,579 --> 00:40:14,832
Stay, stay.
I'll go.

370
00:40:20,462 --> 00:40:21,380
Hi.

371
00:40:24,758 --> 00:40:25,759
And you are?

372
00:40:25,884 --> 00:40:28,011
The new cook.

373
00:40:28,136 --> 00:40:30,556
Is Monsieur Frank in?

374
00:40:30,639 --> 00:40:33,892
Ah! Monsieur Frank.

375
00:40:33,976 --> 00:40:37,062
Is your invitation
for coffee still open?

376
00:40:37,145 --> 00:40:38,772
Sure, come on.
Please, sit.

377
00:40:41,441 --> 00:40:42,401
Madeleine?

378
00:40:42,484 --> 00:40:43,402
Homemade?

379
00:40:43,485 --> 00:40:44,778
Lai:
Yes.

380
00:40:44,903 --> 00:40:46,613
I'll bring some more.

381
00:40:46,697 --> 00:40:47,739
Ah.

382
00:40:47,823 --> 00:40:49,700
My mother used to make...

383
00:40:49,825 --> 00:40:51,076
fresh Madeleines every morning.

384
00:40:51,160 --> 00:40:53,287
I smell them
and my whole childhood...

385
00:40:53,412 --> 00:40:55,414
comes back in one big flood...

386
00:40:55,539 --> 00:40:57,166
like Proust.

387
00:40:57,291 --> 00:40:58,917
You ever read Proust,
Monsieur Frank?

388
00:40:59,001 --> 00:41:00,460
No.

389
00:41:00,586 --> 00:41:01,753
Ah. He's fantastic.

390
00:41:01,837 --> 00:41:03,755
Memory like a steel trap.

391
00:41:03,839 --> 00:41:05,382
He would have been a great cop.

392
00:41:05,465 --> 00:41:06,466
A real detail man.

393
00:41:06,550 --> 00:41:08,093
- Milk?
- Please. Mmm.

394
00:41:09,928 --> 00:41:13,098
Thank you.
Ahh.

395
00:41:13,182 --> 00:41:15,601
Tarconi:
I used to have a memory like Proust.

396
00:41:15,684 --> 00:41:17,811
Like a filing cabinet up there.

397
00:41:17,936 --> 00:41:20,439
I would see something
and remember it like that.

398
00:41:20,522 --> 00:41:22,065
Like, uh, license plates.

399
00:41:22,191 --> 00:41:25,152
I could see a plate
and it was printed in my head.

400
00:41:25,235 --> 00:41:27,112
Now I need all
the help I can get...

401
00:41:27,196 --> 00:41:28,780
remembering whose plate...

402
00:41:28,906 --> 00:41:30,282
goes with whose car.

403
00:41:30,365 --> 00:41:33,410
Like, uh, this one.

404
00:41:35,704 --> 00:41:36,663
It's mine.

405
00:41:36,788 --> 00:41:39,041
Ah, memories.

406
00:41:39,166 --> 00:41:40,334
Frank:
So?

407
00:41:40,417 --> 00:41:41,585
Where's the rest
of the car?

408
00:41:41,668 --> 00:41:43,587
I was hoping
you could tell me.

409
00:41:43,670 --> 00:41:45,172
- It was stolen.
- Stolen?

410
00:41:45,255 --> 00:41:47,299
Yeah, I went down to Frejus
to pick up a few things.

411
00:41:47,382 --> 00:41:48,800
When I came out
of the market, it was...

412
00:41:48,884 --> 00:41:51,803
Gone.
Did you report it?

413
00:41:51,887 --> 00:41:54,973
It's the first on my list
of things to do today.

414
00:41:55,057 --> 00:41:55,974
It's a long walk
from Frejus.

415
00:41:56,058 --> 00:41:57,017
How did you get home?

416
00:41:57,142 --> 00:41:58,310
Well...

417
00:41:58,393 --> 00:42:00,854
I brought him.

418
00:42:00,938 --> 00:42:03,315
I saw him walking
along the dark road.

419
00:42:03,398 --> 00:42:05,400
Mm, a risky thing.

420
00:42:05,526 --> 00:42:07,820
Picking up a stranger
on a dark road.

421
00:42:08,987 --> 00:42:10,823
He had a kind face.

422
00:42:14,409 --> 00:42:16,078
I didn't see
a car outside.

423
00:42:16,203 --> 00:42:17,329
It's in the garage.

424
00:42:17,412 --> 00:42:18,330
May I see it?

425
00:42:18,413 --> 00:42:19,706
Mm-hmm.

426
00:42:40,018 --> 00:42:42,688
Pretty nice car
for a cook.

427
00:42:44,940 --> 00:42:47,734
Some people have a problem
with the Germans.

428
00:42:47,860 --> 00:42:48,986
They're too aggressive.

429
00:42:49,111 --> 00:42:51,405
They take up
the best beaches in summer.

430
00:42:51,488 --> 00:42:53,532
They can't cook worth a damn.

431
00:42:56,702 --> 00:42:58,871
I say anyone
who makes such great cars...

432
00:42:58,954 --> 00:43:01,665
can't be all bad.

433
00:43:01,748 --> 00:43:03,417
I would say your intuition
worked out very well...

434
00:43:03,542 --> 00:43:04,501
for Monsieur Frank,
mademoiselle.

435
00:43:06,211 --> 00:43:08,881
Worked out for both of us.

436
00:43:13,343 --> 00:43:15,262
Bon.

437
00:43:15,345 --> 00:43:17,598
My intuition says
this is probably a good time...

438
00:43:17,681 --> 00:43:20,100
for me to go
file my report.

439
00:43:20,225 --> 00:43:21,685
Where's the rest
of my car?

440
00:43:21,768 --> 00:43:23,061
Oh, yes.

441
00:43:23,145 --> 00:43:24,646
I almost forgot.

442
00:43:24,771 --> 00:43:26,982
It was blown to pieces
at a rest stop.

443
00:43:28,317 --> 00:43:31,278
What's left of it
is down at the lab.

444
00:43:31,361 --> 00:43:33,822
They're trying to separate
what was left...

445
00:43:33,947 --> 00:43:35,908
of the 2 cops in the trunk...

446
00:43:35,991 --> 00:43:38,076
from the rest of it.

447
00:43:38,202 --> 00:43:40,996
But, uh, you wouldn't know
anything about that?

448
00:43:41,121 --> 00:43:42,789
No.

449
00:43:42,873 --> 00:43:44,291
Sorry to interrupt.

450
00:43:44,416 --> 00:43:46,960
Thank you for the coffee
and the memories.

451
00:43:47,085 --> 00:43:48,795
Come back any time.

452
00:43:48,921 --> 00:43:50,797
Would you mind walking me?

453
00:43:50,923 --> 00:43:52,633
Come on.

454
00:43:52,758 --> 00:43:54,218
You have always
been very quiet...

455
00:43:54,343 --> 00:43:56,136
about your business,
Monsieur Frank.

456
00:43:56,261 --> 00:43:59,097
I appreciate that.
Less work for Mother.

457
00:43:59,181 --> 00:44:00,974
But this business
at the rest stop.

458
00:44:01,058 --> 00:44:03,268
That is not very quiet.

459
00:44:03,352 --> 00:44:05,020
I don't suppose you
would like to tell me...

460
00:44:05,145 --> 00:44:07,523
something besides
a stolen car story?

461
00:44:07,648 --> 00:44:09,358
If I had one I would.

462
00:44:09,483 --> 00:44:12,277
Well, may I suggest
that when the 2 of you...

463
00:44:12,361 --> 00:44:14,154
show up in my office
after lunch...

464
00:44:14,238 --> 00:44:15,823
you do have one.

465
00:44:15,948 --> 00:44:18,450
A better one
than you currently have.

466
00:44:25,207 --> 00:44:27,459
You are the one
he wants to see...

467
00:44:27,543 --> 00:44:28,460
not me!

468
00:44:28,544 --> 00:44:30,003
Quiet!

469
00:44:30,087 --> 00:44:32,130
Please, I have to think.

470
00:44:32,256 --> 00:44:34,174
You were supposed
to think last night.

471
00:44:34,258 --> 00:44:36,677
Yeah, well,
last night I had nightmares...

472
00:44:36,760 --> 00:44:39,805
about a girl who came
into my nice, quiet life...

473
00:44:39,888 --> 00:44:41,348
screwed it all up.

474
00:44:41,473 --> 00:44:42,558
Everything she touched broke...

475
00:44:42,683 --> 00:44:44,518
and every move she made
turned into a catastrophe.

476
00:44:44,643 --> 00:44:46,854
OK. Sorry.

477
00:44:49,231 --> 00:44:51,608
I'm still wondering
if I want to know everything...

478
00:44:51,692 --> 00:44:53,819
or nothing about you.

479
00:45:02,327 --> 00:45:03,912
What?

480
00:45:04,037 --> 00:45:05,414
The quiet.

481
00:45:05,539 --> 00:45:07,791
I thought you liked quiet.

482
00:45:10,794 --> 00:45:13,589
Yeah, not this quiet.

483
00:45:16,592 --> 00:45:17,509
Aah!

484
00:45:33,442 --> 00:45:34,318
You OK?

485
00:45:34,443 --> 00:45:35,319
No!

486
00:45:35,444 --> 00:45:36,695
